        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 1:41AM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 141 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles west of Cottonwood, or 18 miles west of Philip, moving north at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cottonwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
